The paper deals with semantic image segmentation, which is a computer vision task, hence cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Conditional Random Fields (CRFs) and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are both popular machine learning techniques, making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of backpropagation for optimization, which is a common technique in neural networks, further supporting cs.NE as a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as part-of-speech tagging, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL.
